text: The Hays-Kiser House is a historic house in Antioch, Tennessee, U.S.. It was built in 1795 for Charles Hays, a settler from North Carolina. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since September 10, 1974. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Tennessee Category:Federal architecture in Tennessee Category:Houses completed in 1795 Category:Buildings and structures in Davidson County, Tennessee
